<h1>MVP vs Prototype Alignment Notes (v0.5) - Comprehensive</h1>
<p>Source document: Set The Table - MVP Technical Requirements Document - Working Draft v0.5 (Prepared 2026-03-22)</p>
<p>Prototype analyzed: STT React prototype in C:\Users\Blvk Inc\Desktop\Stt</p>
<p>Analysis date: 2026-03-23</p>
<p>Note: The prototype is front-end only. Data is stored in localStorage and no backend workflows, emails, or Stripe integration are present.</p>
<p>Status legend:</p>
<ul>
<li>Implemented: UI plus working client-side logic that demonstrates the requirement in the prototype.</li>
<li>UI-only: Screens or inputs exist, but no real data model enforcement or backend support.</li>
<li>Partial: Some fields or flows exist, but key parts of the requirement are missing.</li>
<li>Not implemented: The requirement is not present in the prototype.</li>
<li>Conflict with MVP: The prototype includes opposite scope or a future-phase feature.</li>
<li>Out of scope but present: MVP explicitly excludes it, yet the prototype includes it.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Prototype snapshot (routes, data, and key behaviors)</h2>
<ul>
<li>Customer routes: /, /explore, /events, /events/:id, /venues, /venues/:id, /packages/:eventId, /packages/detail/:packageId, /booking/:id, /profile, /auth, /premium, /review/:bookingId, /cart, /cart/checkout.</li>
<li>Merchant routes: /merchant/auth, /merchant/onboarding, /merchant/dashboard, /merchant/events, /merchant/events/create, /merchant/events/:id/edit, /merchant/events/:id, /merchant/packages, /merchant/packages/create, /merchant/packages/:id/edit, /merchant/bookings, /merchant/customers, /merchant/analytics, /merchant/promotions, /merchant/advertising, /merchant/faqs, /merchant/settings, /merchant/profile, /merchant/plans.</li>
<li>Admin routes: /admin/dashboard, /admin/merchants, /admin/merchants/new, /admin/merchants/:id/edit, /admin/users, /admin/events, /admin/approvals, /admin/payments, /admin/analytics, /admin/system, /admin/logs, /admin/reports, /admin/profile, /admin/venues/:venueId.</li>
<li>Storage model: localStorage keys for stt_user, stt_cart, stt_merchant and multiple stt_merchant_* collections.</li>
<li>Demo data: Soft Drinks Package template is reused across two events with different per-event rules in MerchantContext:</li>
<li>Event 101 (one-time) uses inventoryConsumption=per_guest, maxBookingsPerDate=60, cutoffHours=6.</li>
<li>Event 102 (recurring) uses inventoryConsumption=per_package, maxBookingsPerDate=40, cutoffHours=24.</li>
<li>Cart behavior: CartPage supports per-item checkout and an aggregated "Checkout All" flow (multi-checkout UX).</li>
<li>Date gating: EventDetailsPage requires a date selection before package selection.</li>
</ul>
<h2>MVP design principles vs prototype</h2>
<ul>
<li>Admin-first launch: Conflict. Prototype includes merchant self-service portal and onboarding.</li>
<li>Venue-first MVP model: Partial. Prototype centers merchants; venue records exist but are not admin-first.</li>
<li>Future merchant compatibility: Partial. Prototype uses merchantId in event objects but does not model venue-claim.</li>
<li>Normalized package architecture: Partial. Package templates exist and are reused across events.</li>
<li>Occurrence-level inventory: Not implemented.</li>
<li>Default + exception occurrence control: Not implemented.</li>
<li>Operational availability controls: Not implemented.</li>
<li>Per-event-package payment control: Not implemented.</li>
<li>Mixed-cart privacy by venue: Not implemented.</li>
<li>Structured customer data ownership: Not implemented.</li>
<li>Venue-level financial ownership: Partial. Merchant settings capture banking, but not in admin portal.</li>
<li>Event-level availability control: Not implemented.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Actor model alignment</h2>
<ul>
<li>Customer: Implemented as UI-only (customer website, auth, cart, booking, profile).</li>
<li>STT Super Admin: Implemented as UI-only (admin portal routes).</li>
<li>STT Admin: Not implemented as a distinct role.</li>
<li>STT Editor: Not implemented.</li>
<li>STT Bookings &amp; Customer Manager: Not implemented.</li>
<li>Merchant organization (future phase): Conflict. Prototype includes full merchant onboarding and portal.</li>
</ul>
