<h2>API and service boundary alignment (Section 8)</h2>
<p>All API layers described in the MVP are not implemented in the prototype because there is no backend. The prototype provides only UI surfaces for some of the domains.</p>
<ul>
<li>Identity &amp; Access: UI-only (AuthPage, AuthContext).</li>
<li>Customer Profile &amp; Address: UI-only (ProfilePage).</li>
<li>Catalog: UI-only (EventsPage, VenuesPage, EventDetailsPage).</li>
<li>Package &amp; Pricing: UI-only (Merchant package templates and rule UI).</li>
<li>Occurrence &amp; Inventory: Not implemented.</li>
<li>Cart &amp; Booking: UI-only (CartContext, BookingContext).</li>
<li>Payments &amp; Payouts: UI-only (BookingPage, CartCheckoutPage, admin payments pages).</li>
<li>Notifications: Not implemented.</li>
<li>Reporting: UI-only (admin analytics/reports pages).</li>
</ul>
<h2>Non-functional requirements (Section 9)</h2>
<ul>
<li>Extensible for future merchant portal: Partial. Prototype already includes merchant portal, but no venue-claim model.</li>
<li>Referential integrity across venue/event/occurrence/package/booking/payment: Not implemented.</li>
<li>Transaction-safe inventory updates: Not implemented.</li>
<li>Stripe webhook as payment source of truth: Not implemented.</li>
<li>Auditable admin actions: Not implemented.</li>
<li>Structured recurrence/occurrence with default + overrides: Not implemented.</li>
<li>Manual sold-out/unavailable controls at package and event level: Not implemented.</li>
<li>Reporting uses normalized data: Not implemented.</li>
<li>Event-driven email integrations with failure logging: Not implemented.</li>
<li>Venue data isolation in mixed-venue orders: Not implemented.</li>
<li>Mixed-payment orders with per-line tracking: Not implemented.</li>
<li>Commission per booking line with manual payouts: Not implemented.</li>
</ul>
<h2>MVP exclusions (Section 10) vs prototype</h2>
<ul>
<li>Merchant self-service portal and login: Out of scope but present (/merchant/*).</li>
<li>Merchant onboarding, KYB, business-license collection: Out of scope but present (merchant onboarding, settings, trade license upload UI).</li>
<li>Venue claim flow: Out of scope and not present.</li>
<li>Premium customer plans: Out of scope but present (/premium).</li>
<li>Rewards / referrals: Out of scope but present (Profile rewards UI).</li>
<li>Customer reviews: Out of scope but present (/review/:bookingId, reviews in event details).</li>
<li>Advertising / ads manager: Out of scope but present (/merchant/advertising, /merchant/promotions).</li>
<li>Community / forum / messaging: Out of scope and not present.</li>
<li>Native app / in-app notifications: Out of scope and not present.</li>
<li>Refund-status view: Out of scope and not present.</li>
<li>Merchant analytics: Out of scope but present (/merchant/analytics).</li>
<li>Automated shared-capacity optimizer: Out of scope and not present.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Remaining implementation decisions (Section 11)</h2>
<p>The prototype does not address any of the open decision areas in the MVP document.</p>
<ul>
<li>Rule conflict precedence: Not defined.</li>
<li>Recurring occurrence materialization horizon: Not defined.</li>
<li>Cancellation request policy (cutoffs/refund behavior): Not defined.</li>
<li>Customer churn definition: Not defined.</li>
<li>Media handling method (upload vs embed): Not defined.</li>
<li>Accessibility data structure (free text vs structured): Not defined.</li>
<li>Advanced shared-capacity policy (future): Not defined.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Key mismatches and gaps to highlight</h2>
<ul>
<li>The MVP is admin-first and venue-first with no merchant portal. The prototype is merchant-centric and includes onboarding, settings, and plans.</li>
<li>Recurrence, occurrence-level inventory, and availability are central MVP requirements but are not implemented in the prototype.</li>
<li>Mixed payment modes, deposit handling, and Stripe payment workflows are not implemented.</li>
<li>Customer data capture requirements (DOB, nationality, residency, WhatsApp, Teacher/Cabin Crew) are missing.</li>
<li>Global categories, SEO fields, and reusable FAQs are missing or only present in merchant UI.</li>
<li>Venue-scoped privacy for multi-venue orders is not implemented.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Summary</h2>
<p>The prototype demonstrates a strong UI foundation for discovery, booking, cart, and a full merchant portal. However, the MVP document is explicitly admin-first with deeper recurrence, inventory, and rule engine requirements that are largely absent from the prototype. The largest alignment risk is the mismatch between the MVP operating model (admin-only venue setup) and the prototype's merchant self-service model. The next alignment step is to either scope the prototype as "post-MVP" or add admin-first workflows with occurrence-level inventory, payment-mode handling, and complete customer data capture.</p>
</body></html>

